com.facebook.buck.android

Class AndroidManifest

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.facebook.buck.rules.AbstractBuildable
      • com.facebook.buck.android.AndroidManifest
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Buildable

    public class AndroidManifest
extends AbstractBuildable
    AndroidManifest is a Buildable that can generate an Android manifest from a skeleton manifest and the library manifests from its dependencies. 
     android_manifest(
   name = 'my_manifest',
   skeleton = 'AndroidManifestSkeleton.xml',
   deps = [
     ':sample_manifest',
     # Additional dependent android_resource and android_library rules would be listed here,
     # as well.
   ],
 )
    This will produce a genfile that will be parameterized by the name of the android_manifest rule. This can be used as follows: 
     android_binary(
   name = 'my_app',
   manifest = genfile('AndroidManifest__my_manifest__.xml'),
   deps = [
     ':my_manifest',
   ],
 )

      • getInputsToCompareToOutput

        public Collection<Path> getInputsToCompareToOutput()
        Description copied from interface: Buildable
        Get the set of input files whose contents should be hashed for the purpose of determining whether this rule is cached.

        Note that inputs are iterable and should generally be alphabetized so that lists with the same elements will be .equals() to one another. However, for some build rules (such as Genrule), the order of the inputs is significant and in these cases the inputs may be ordered in any way the rule feels most appropriate.

        Overrides:

        Returns:
